UNDERSTANDING RESTATEMENT
Product: distribution/install.sh + lang/{en,ro,ru} + README.{en,ro,ru}.md + dry-run.sh
  sandbox harness — the working, testable installer kit for a stranger with no
  author contact. Acceptance = parent ATOM-100 H1-H11 (hard) + S1-S3 (soft,
  judged by Verify/CEO, not self-closable). Deliver only under distribution/**
  and this atom's own folder. No git commands. Blind verify (ATOM-101-VERIFY);
  my products speak alone, no verifier conversation.
Seven-point interview (closed list, H2): language(en/ro/ru) -> workdir ->
  Claude Code check -> subscription check -> Telegram opt-in (BotFather walk,
  live getMe) -> telemetry opt-in (show-what-leaves first) -> heartbeat
  consent (benefit-framed, default hint yes). Zero questions outside these.
State machine (H3/H8): install-state.json, check->do idempotent steps, rerun
  resumes without re-asking, healthy rerun = free health-check.
Failure ladder (H9): self-diagnose -> auto-attempt (network retry/lock/perm
  hint) -> concrete human action; max 2 auto-attempts/step, 3rd always human.
Secrets (H4): bot token file mode 600 in user's workspace; never in
  state/log/telemetry/git; negative grep empty across all four.
Finale (H5): print handoff to "qroky start" in chosen language.
Self-update (H11): heartbeat pulse -> git fetch --tags (release tags only,
  never main) -> digest (3-line changelog + да/позже/подробнее) -> apply only
  on explicit да, mini-atom writes decisions/ record in USER's workspace,
  reconciliation of local edits shown before apply, conflicts never silently
  overwritten.
Harness (INFO-025, 9-point checklist) must be walked and logged before any
  scenario touches "real" data — sandbox only, Claude Code / Telegram probes
  stubbed behind marked test hooks (QROKY_TEST_STUBS=1 and PATH-shadow fakes),
  real code paths stay honest per role instructions.

