- FINDING (real near-miss, corrected before it reached the harness): this
  smoke test did NOT shadow `launchctl` on PATH, and the answer sequence hit
  "yes" on the heartbeat opt-in — install.sh's real `launchctl bootstrap`
  call registered a real LaunchAgent (md.qroky.heartbeat.qroky) in THIS
  machine's actual launchd session, even though $HOME was overridden to a
  sandbox path (launchd's gui/<uid> target is session-scoped, not affected
  by $HOME). Caught immediately, removed with `launchctl bootout`, verified
  clean via `launchctl list`. Lesson applied: the real dry-run.sh harness
  MUST shadow `launchctl` on PATH exactly like `claude`/`crontab` are
  shadowed in 071's precedent — never let install.sh's real launchctl run
  during any scripted scenario. Logged per harness-checklist point 8
  (verify before first live run) — this IS that verification catching a
  real defect before it reached a scenario transcript.
- Wrote distribution/dry-run.sh (519 lines) implementing all 7 scenarios
  named in INPUT section 2 (full clean run, kill-mid-install, healthy
  rerun, broken dependency, idempotency diff, secrets negative grep,
  self-update) plus the H2 question-inventory check, against a
  fully-stubbed sandbox (claude/curl/launchctl shadowed on PATH, offline
  tagged git repo standing in for the framework source, isolated HOME).
  First run: 5/8 checks passed, 3 failed -- all three were real bugs in
  either install.sh or dry-run.sh, not spec gaps:
    (a) `VAR=val cmd1 | cmd2` in bash only exports VAR for cmd1, never for
        cmd2 -- every `QROKY_WORKSPACE_DIR="$W" printf ... | install.sh`
        one-liner in the harness silently failed to pass the workdir
        override, so every scenario after the first was actually reusing
        ONE real leftover workspace via install.sh's own pointer-file
        fallback. This produced a REAL stray directory
        (distribution/qroky/, with a real vendored framework, a real
        token file, etc.) on THIS machine's actual disk during testing --
        caught, understood, cleaned up (rm -rf distribution/qroky
        distribution/.qroky-workdir-pointer), and fixed at the root:
        every env-var-scoped call in dry-run.sh now goes through a
        run_install() helper that uses a real subshell export.
    (b) install.sh's four flag-driven commands (--check-update,
        --show-update-details, --apply-update, --enable-heartbeat) called
        state_load before STATE_FILE was ever computed for them (that
        computation lived only in the interview's resume path) -- an
        "unbound variable" crash under set -u. Fixed by factoring a
        shared resolve_and_load_state() that resolves the workdir the
        same way the interview does (env override > pointer file >
        ./qroky default) before loading.
    (c) the failure ladder (run_with_ladder) gave up after only 1 retry
        instead of 2 (off-by-one in the attempt-counting condition) --
        fixed (attempt >= 3, i.e. first try + 2 retries = 3 total tries,
        matching H9's "max 2 auto-attempts, 3rd failure always to human"
        literally).
    (d) grep -rc on a single file (not a directory) printed a
        "path:count" line on this machine's grep instead of a bare count,
        breaking the secrets-negative-grep scenario's numeric comparison
        -- fixed (dropped -r, the target was never a directory).
    (e) L_UPDATE_AVAILABLE's `cat <<EOF ... %s ... EOF` never substitutes
        %s (that is a printf idiom, not a heredoc one) -- the digest was
        printing literal "%s -> %s" instead of the two version numbers.
        Fixed in all three lang files: the function now takes real
        positional args ($1/$2/$3) interpolated directly in the heredoc.
  Second full run after all five fixes: 8/8 PASS, zero stray files, zero
